Last desk reset of 2025

Have a great Sunday ✌🏼

#reset #desksetup #clean #lifestyle

You don’t need fancy gear to start creating, but having the right basics helps.

Following up on my last reel, here’s my beginner-friendly content creation kit 👇

📱 Your phone — more than enough for 90% of the content you’ll ever shoot
🎥 A mobile gimbal — skip the latest model, older versions work just as well
🎙️ A portable mic — clean audio instantly levels up your videos
📐 A solid tripod — don’t pay full price, they’re always on sale
💻 A reliable computer — where everything comes together (Optional since you can do a lot on your phone with CapCut and Instagram Edits)
☕️ (Optional) loads of coffee 😜

Start with what you have. Upgrade when it makes sense

caption:
With all the sales going on right now, it’s tempting to think you need new gear to start posting.

But the truth is, you probably don’t.

One of the most common mistakes (and yes, I’ve been guilty of this too) is believing that better gear automatically means better results. Most of the time, that’s just not true.

Natural light + your phone camera is more than enough to get started.

Upgrade only when it’s actually necessary. Until then, save your money and focus on creating.

Also, this is my first sit-down, talking-to-camera video. One of my goals this year is to get more comfortable doing these sit-down, talking videos.

Create first. Optimize later.

Cheers 🤝 

#contentcreator #tech #learning #deinfluencing #journey
